     else { return &quot;&quot; }<br>    return dobString<br>}()<br></p><p>But if serverDateFormatter is actually a NSDateFormatter instance, which does not return optionals, then you&#39;d want to go with:<br></p><p>let dobString: String = {<br>    guard let dob = dob else { return &quot;&quot; }<br>    return serverDateFormatter.string(from:dob)<br>}()<br></p><p>-- E<br>-------------- next part --------------<br>An HTML attachment was scrubbed...<br>URL: &lt;https://lists.swift.org/pipermail/swift-users/attachments/20160804/379f69a8/attachment.html&gt;<br></p></div></li></ul></li></ul></div>    </main>
